assessment_details.task_description:
The aim of this assessment task is to increase the students's knowledge across the breadth of the Course content. This is achieved by a combination of:

pre-reading of the specified chapter of the text (Lawrence and Weber, 2017);

completion of the Learning Unit pro forma for that week;

pre-reading of the set Case Study;

active discussion of the set Case Study in the seminar; and

making notes during the Seminar discussion in the pro forma for that Case Study.

Students are required to submit 8 items for assessment as advised on Blackboard. Assessment of the mark awarded to the individual student is based upon both the two pro forma papers submitted by the individual student that week, namely:

the completed Learning Unit pro forma for that week; and

the completed Case study discussion paper pro forma.
